author: jdcasey
msg: Resolving: MNG-495
o Pressing [ENTER] at a plugin update prompt should result in the plugin being registered, as indicated by the prompt.
o Use CLI switch '--no-plugin-updates' to suppress usage of the plugin registry
o Use CLI switch '--update-plugins' to force updated/resolved plugin versions to be registered
o Neither of these has a short CLI option, since we're starting to run out of sensible char options for these types of things.

author: ekoneil
msg: Initial checkin of new WSM annotation processor prototype.
This is currently *incomplete* but has the framework in place to do annotation processing and code generation in three stages:
- checking
- model construction (via JavaBeans and a factory)
- generation
using four distinct pieces of code:
- Jsr181AnnotationChecker
- model/factory/BeehiveWsMetadataFactory
- BeehiveWs* JavaBeans
- AxisGenerator (need a base class for this)
Lots of stuff is undone -- handling endpoint interfaces, some annotation checking, a generation abstraction, etc.
BB: self
DRT: sandbox/ekoneil pass (all but WSM)
